Fatima, the daughter of the All Progressives Congress vice-presidential candidate, Kashim Shettima, is set to get married. The wedding Fatiha is scheduled to hold on Saturday, July 30th, 2022 at the Shehu’s Palace in Maiduguri, Borno State.  She will marry her fiancé, Sadiq Ibrahim Bunu.The groom’s father is Ibrahim Bunu, an architect and a former Minister of the Federal Capital Territory (FCT).Bunu served from May 1999 until February 2001 in the cabinet of President Olusegun Obasanjo. He was said to have designed the Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC) Towers in Abuja. Shettima was officially unveiled as APC vice presidential candidate on Wednesday at the Shehu Musa Yar’Adua Centre in Abuja. Tinubu, the presidential candidate of the party, who is a Muslim, has insisted on having him, a fellow Muslim, as his running mate. Tinubu is from Southern Nigeria while Shettima, a former Borno governor, is from the Muslim-dominated Northern part of the country.